	<td style="width: 50%;" class="kmd-standard-padding ">

	

  <h4 class="kmd-paragraph-title">Revolutionary parental controls with Amazon FreeTime</h4>
  <p class="kmd-text-paragraph-body ">Amazon FreeTime is built from the ground up to help give parents peace of mind when it comes to tablet use. Parents can create a profile for each of their children and choose what books, apps, games, and videos they want to give their kids access to. Amazon FreeTime is free on every new Fire tablet.</p>


	

  <h4 class="kmd-paragraph-title">Designed with kids in mind</h4>
  <p class="kmd-text-paragraph-body ">When kids use Amazon FreeTime, it's like they have their very own personalized tablet. The background color and fonts change to a kid-friendly design, they only see the titles that they have access to see, the home screen carousel shows their recently viewed titles, and they can even navigate visually to content based on characters or topics—for example "Cinderella," "Dinosaurs," or "Puppies."</p>


	

  <h4 class="kmd-paragraph-title">Set screen limits</h4>
  <p class="kmd-text-paragraph-body kmd-paragraph-last">Many parents choose to limit their kids' screen time, but doing so without the proper tools is difficult. With Amazon FreeTime, parents can set daily limits for tablet use, or restrict certain categories—like games and video—while leaving unlimited time for reading.

